# Set Up Prometheus Metrics

## Arguments
- `service`: Service name to instrument

## Architecture

```
Request → httpMetrics middleware → handler → response
                                    ↓
                              Prometheus counters/histograms
                                    ↓
                             GET /metrics → prom-client → scrape
```

## Steps

### 1. Add Dependencies
- Add `@ironplate/metrics` to `apps/{service}/package.json`
- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} install`

### 2. Create Metrics Plugin

```typescript
import type { IPlugin, PluginContext } from '@ironplate/service';
import { createMetricsRegistry, createHttpMetrics, createMetricsEndpoint } from '@ironplate/metrics';

export const metricsPlugin: IPlugin = {
  name: 'metrics',
  order: 10,
  async initialize(ctx: PluginContext) {
    const registry = createMetricsRegistry({
      serviceName: ctx.config.name,
      defaultMetrics: true,
    });

    // RED metrics middleware
    const { middleware } = createHttpMetrics(registry, {
      serviceName: ctx.config.name,
      excludePaths: ['/healthz', '/readyz', '/metrics'],
    });
    ctx.addMiddleware({ handler: middleware, order: 10 });

    // Expose /metrics endpoint (no auth)
    ctx.addRoutes({
      path: '/',
      router: createMetricsEndpoint(registry),
      skipAuth: true,
    });

    // Share registry with other plugins
    ctx.registerService('metricsRegistry', registry);
  },
};
```

### 3. Register Plugin

```typescript
import { createService } from '@ironplate/service';
import { metricsPlugin } from './plugins/metrics';

const service = await createService('{service}')
  .use(metricsPlugin)
  .routes('/api', apiRouter)
  .build();
```

### 4. Add Custom Metrics

```typescript
import client from 'prom-client';

// Get shared registry from plugin context
const registry = service.getService<client.Registry>('metricsRegistry')!;

const ordersProcessed = new client.Counter({
  name: 'orders_processed_total',
  help: 'Total number of orders processed',
  labelNames: ['status'],
  registers: [registry],
});

// In handler:
ordersProcessed.inc({ status: 'success' });
```

## Default Metrics Exposed

| Metric | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `http_request_duration_seconds` | Histogram | Request latency |
| `http_requests_total` | Counter | Total request count |
| `http_request_errors_total` | Counter | Requests with status >= 400 |
| `nodejs_*` | Various | Node.js runtime metrics (GC, event loop, memory) |

## CRITICAL Rules
- ALWAYS exclude `/healthz`, `/readyz`, `/metrics` from HTTP metrics
- ALWAYS register the metrics plugin with `order: 10` (before auth)
- ALWAYS expose `/metrics` without authentication (Prometheus needs to scrape it)
- Use labels sparingly — high cardinality labels cause memory issues
- NEVER use user IDs, request IDs, or unbounded values as labels

## Checklist
- [ ] `@ironplate/metrics` dependency added
- [ ] Metrics plugin created and registered
- [ ] `/metrics` endpoint exposed without auth
- [ ] RED metrics recording request rate, errors, duration
- [ ] Custom business metrics added if needed
- [ ] Prometheus ServiceMonitor configured in Helm values
